[tool-call] delta {"path":"tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggerListenerImplStubTest.java","edits":[{"oldText":"import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInput;","newText":"import java.io.ObjectInput;"},{"oldText":"import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;","newText":"import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;\nimport java.net.JarURLConnection;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;"},{"oldText":"    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.findClass(name);\n            }\n\n            byte[] classBytes = readStubClassBytes();\n            return defineClass(name, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] readStubClassBytes() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            try (InputStream inputStream = getParent().getResourceAsStream(STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE)) {\n                if (inputStream == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME);\n                }\n                return inputStream.readAllBytes();\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME, e);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n","newText":"    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) throws IOException {\n            super(new URL[] { classPathRoot(parent) }, parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        private static URL classPathRoot(ClassLoader parent) throws IOException {\n            URL resource = parent.getResource(STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE);\n            if (resource == null) {\n                throw new IOException(\"Unable to locate \" + STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE);\n            }\n            if (\"jar\".equals(resource.getProtocol())) {\n                JarURLConnection connection = (JarURLConnection) resource.openConnection();\n                return connection.getJarFileURL();\n            }\n\n            String externalForm = resource.toExternalForm();\n            String root = externalForm.substring(0, externalForm.length() - STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE.length());\n            return new URL(root);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}
[tool-call] end id=call_gaIK4uExd0SNKC4VyliCxXnl|fc_0724d5a6901117010169f4a0659ef081a2bd5852d3f631ede9 name=edit args={"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggerListenerImplStubTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInput;", "newText": "import java.io.ObjectInput;"}, {"oldText": "import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;", "newText": "import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;\nimport java.net.JarURLConnection;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.findClass(name);\n            }\n\n            byte[] classBytes = readStubClassBytes();\n            return defineClass(name, classBytes, 0, classBytes.length);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] readStubClassBytes() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            try (InputStream inputStream = getParent().getResourceAsStream(STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE)) {\n                if (inputStream == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME);\n                }\n                return inputStream.readAllBytes();\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(STUB_CLASS_NAME, e);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) throws IOException {\n            super(new URL[] { classPathRoot(parent) }, parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        private static URL classPathRoot(ClassLoader parent) throws IOException {\n            URL resource = parent.getResource(STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE);\n            if (resource == null) {\n                throw new IOException(\"Unable to locate \" + STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE);\n            }\n            if (\"jar\".equals(resource.getProtocol())) {\n                JarURLConnection connection = (JarURLConnection) resource.openConnection();\n                return connection.getJarFileURL();\n            }\n\n            String externalForm = resource.toExternalForm();\n            String root = externalForm.substring(0, externalForm.length() - STUB_CLASS_RESOURCE.length());\n            return new URL(root);\n        }\n    }\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering refinements**\n\nI'm thinking about what refinements are acceptable. It seems like using order and ensureInitialized is a good approach. I could consider adding a standard URLClassLoader with a child-first strategy to minimize the risk of instrumentation issues. I'm focusing on utilizing java.net.URLClassLoader with the library JAR URL sourced from resources. There’s a lot here to think about for the best implementation!\n\n**Considering class loading behavior**\n\nI'm thinking about how the `Class.forName(\"freemarker.debug.DebuggerListener\")` within the `clinit` method uses the caller's defining loader, namely the `URLClassLoader`. It attempts to load the class for any dependencies, while respecting the parent class loader's hierarchy. If the name isn't a stub, it appears to prioritize the parent's loading mechanism, which seems reasonable. Okay, it looks like I need to make some edits to refine this further!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0724d5a6901117010169f4a04aa7bc81a29da1613f69816218\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9KBlNbq02mk7_da9mcHYG3GnBBgcN9grEzN2VpH9ZP7sBILAS8bQ20oS6v790p-6HozXB02zRN3KVBI64GkiWXkjn4YIa-5SZ37j4MbC8EsPCEz78fX03MaQva8oMFnQFhVOO68V9bV6MFmqwutCiaxX-0ugDGjWFhgP-TK0bw1ltFpS5IQWcBK-ZZeCnUXks34QVA3ob2xv9nRYWepcF0y7BZt7ppYpeVAxCNcl2z9L1WyGi2MdmUr1dwQ1so0HcJKO6cXqAbHVwkfpwxqpB6wWtZG6FnAHTz33cwsuCH5JxiyzoZoIf13nJr6ElyVctZ6IZoiwU7egZ7IdJJgzoEuQKr3fPbX4eYmfvc3ijnbmohvkM6QaFYzFfyN5ztv-BYMsZVx-ZlgCMe_K-5hHBYUdZp5Ky1aQfCOBcCIhCjGgyXWB9i44A2OtBnSe7hjc6kSu9wJP4-stYR6BofBRNyNe2nfYUgpvqx_YZHxvtF71kanJ8hIC6d80cG4NnmX4BGsrohzvRmIiiU1aMIUmtqb5j8jUXW3Z6J9DapEpem5qraSYBWzbbXbnTGooAuTrt68jJ60H0IyOf4iIWaKWbHc2-Pbvpi-CFss89UFEsbCzd43SHmse13-EqvgF1npqeXIhdnm0IC_843Jk3VcSIBHJw41eUMeXzUaLxPm9x8PURLRP3ikj3AThWBQCne4kb7MSD0-kZTdW4O2vqcTvg9P2p9EHkRlSqnVqj9gU7f-HakJ3jsipu-9nwP1v1Zwv3MXhGsxZVarnNn-heNlgFZFd_oYrMGUYgyoHE