entation!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading behavior**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how the `Class.forName(\\\"freemarker.debug.DebuggerListener\\\")` within the `clinit` method uses the caller's defining loader, namely the `URLClassLoader`. It attempts to load the class for any dependencies, while respecting the parent class loader's hierarchy. If the name isn't a stub, it appears to prioritize the parent's loading mechanism, which seems reasonable. Okay, it looks like I need to make some edits to refine this further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gaIK4uExd0SNKC4VyliCxXnl|fc_0724d5a6901117010169f4a0659ef081a2bd5852d3f631ede9", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.freemarker/freemarker/2.3.31/src/test/java/fm/FreemarkerDebugImplRmiDebuggerListenerImplStubTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInput;", "newText": "import java.io.ObjectInput;"}, {"oldText": "import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;", "newText": "import java.rmi.server.RemoteObject;\nimport java.rmi.server.RemoteRef;\nimport java.net.JarURLConnection;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class StubOnlyClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        StubOnlyClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!STUB_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n\n            Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n            if (loadedClass == null) {\n                loadedClass = findClass(name);\n            }\n            if (resolve) {\n                resolveClass(loadedClass);\n            }\n            return loadedClass;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(Strin